# Kconfig for the BTRFS+DwarFS hybrid filesystem framework

config BTRFS_DWARFS
	tristate "BTRFS+DwarFS hybrid filesystem framework"
	depends on BTRFS_FS
	depends on FUSE_FS
	depends on NET
	select NETLINK
	help
	  Provides a framework for blending BTRFS and DwarFS filesystems
	  into a unified namespace.

	  Two partition types are supported:

	    DwarFS-backed: stores BTRFS subvolumes and snapshots as
	    compressed DwarFS image files, providing archival-quality
	    compression (typically 10-16x) for read-mostly data.

	    BTRFS-backed: stores DwarFS image files on a live BTRFS
	    filesystem, giving images CoW semantics, per-file checksums,
	    and snapshot capability.

	  The blend layer merges both partition types into a single
	  coherent namespace with automatic copy-up on write.

	  To compile as a module, choose M. The module will be called
	  btrfs_dwarfs.

	  If unsure, say N.

config BTRFS_DWARFS_DEBUG
	bool "BTRFS+DwarFS debug output"
	depends on BTRFS_DWARFS
	help
	  Enable verbose pr_debug() output from the BTRFS+DwarFS framework.
	  This adds overhead and should only be enabled for development.

	  If unsure, say N.
